{
  "texts": [
    "I believe that an open dialogue about the use of GenAI in research can ultimately help integrating GenAI in our research and elevate the quality of science.",
    "However, in my opinion, this is only possible if we create an environment that enables and encourages us to learn from our mistakes and stimulates early adjustments.",
    "We must start somewhere, as no piece of technology was perfect upon creation.",
    "We must learn from what we see happening now and use those lessons to guide us in the morally right direction.",
    "I see it as a good thing that we are discovering biases in the training data, made-up references and thinking about the consequences of inequal access to knowledge, because this means that we can improve the models and use them with more caution."
  ]
}